00:13:09.221 --> 00:13:11.757
<i> uh, focal dystonias.</i>

00:13:11.857 --> 00:13:15.660 align:start size:91% position:9%
Focal means that it's just
one place in the body.

00:13:15.761 --> 00:13:19.364 align:start size:84% position:16%
<i> Dystonia involves
 abnormal muscle spasms</i>

00:13:19.464 --> 00:13:22.768 line:83%
that lead to, uh,
distorted postures

00:13:22.868 --> 00:13:24.970 line:85%
and abnormal motor control,

00:13:25.070 --> 00:13:27.338 align:start size:88% position:13% line:83%
and these focal dystonias
can involve

00:13:27.439 --> 00:13:29.441 line:83%
different parts
of the body.

00:13:29.541 --> 00:13:31.410 align:start size:78% position:22% line:83%
Uh, one of my
principal interests

00:13:31.510 --> 00:13:34.013 align:start size:84% position:16% line:83%
has been focal dystonia
of the hand.

00:13:36.182 --> 00:13:39.150 align:start size:84% position:16%
<i> One of the most common
 is writer's cramp,</i>

00:13:39.251 --> 00:13:41.587 align:start size:84% position:16%
<i> uh, because people tend
 to write a lot.</i>

00:13:41.687 --> 00:13:44.990
<i> Um, and another
 common disorder</i>

00:13:45.090 --> 00:13:48.193
<i> is different types of
 musician's cramp...</i>

00:13:48.293 --> 00:13:49.494
<i> (playing piano music)</i>

00:13:49.594 --> 00:13:51.396
<i> particularly piano cramp,</i>

00:13:51.496 --> 00:13:54.566
<i> and again, the frequency
 of these focal dystonias</i>

00:13:54.666 --> 00:13:56.835
<i> of the hand relate
 to a certain extent</i>

00:13:56.935 --> 00:13:59.638
<i> to the frequency
 of what people do.</i>

00:13:59.738 --> 00:14:01.039
<i> Writer's cramp
 is most common</i>

00:14:01.139 --> 00:14:03.875
<i> because most people write.</i>

00:14:03.976 --> 00:14:05.643 align:start size:75% position:25%
<i> In terms of
 musicians cramp,</i>

00:14:05.744 --> 00:14:08.480
<i> piano player's cramp
 is the most common,</i>

00:14:08.580 --> 00:14:10.415 align:start size:84% position:16%
<i> because that's the most
 common instrument</i>

00:14:10.515 --> 00:14:11.617
<i> that people play.</i>

00:14:11.717 --> 00:14:13.418
<i> Writers cramp,
 musicians cramp</i>

00:14:13.518 --> 00:14:16.088 align:start size:72% position:28%
<i> are not painful
 situations.</i>

00:14:16.188 --> 00:14:18.156 line:91%
<i> Uh, it appears
 in the patients</i>

00:14:18.256 --> 00:14:20.225 align:start size:78% position:22% line:91%
<i> as a motor control
 problem.</i>

00:14:20.325 --> 00:14:22.861 line:91%
<i> They feel they lose
 control of their hand</i>

00:14:22.962 --> 00:14:24.763 align:start size:75% position:25% line:91%
<i> as they're doing
 an activity,</i>

00:14:24.863 --> 00:14:26.331
<i> but it doesn't hurt.</i>

00:14:26.431 --> 00:14:28.800
<i> Uh, it isn't painful.</i>

00:14:28.900 --> 00:14:31.236 align:start size:78% position:22%
Writer's cramp,
or musician's cramp

00:14:31.336 --> 00:14:32.904
is a cramp
in the brain.

00:14:33.004 --> 00:14:34.539
It's not a cramp
in the muscle.

00:14:34.640 --> 00:14:37.609 align:start size:91% position:9%
<i> Focal dystonia
 is a problem of the brain,</i>

00:14:37.709 --> 00:14:40.779 align:start size:78% position:22%
<i> and specifically
 the brain's control</i>

00:14:40.879 --> 00:14:42.680
<i> of the muscles.</i>

00:14:42.781 --> 00:14:45.183 align:start size:75% position:25%
<i> Obviously,
 when people move,</i>

00:14:45.283 --> 00:14:47.886
<i> those, uh, commands
 to make movements</i>

00:14:47.986 --> 00:14:49.655
<i> come from the brain.</i>

00:14:49.755 --> 00:14:52.123 align:start size:81% position:19%
<i> Uh, mediated through
 the spinal cord,</i>

00:14:52.223 --> 00:14:54.759
<i> so the brain sends signals
 down to the spinal cord,</i>

00:14:54.859 --> 00:14:57.629 align:start size:94% position:6%
<i> the spinal cord
 sends signals to the muscle,</i>

00:14:57.730 --> 00:15:00.799 align:start size:75% position:25%
<i> uh, to cause
 the contraction.</i>

00:15:00.899 --> 00:15:02.801 align:start size:88% position:13%
<i> In dystonia,
 if you look at the brain,</i>

00:15:02.901 --> 00:15:04.503
<i> at least superficially,</i>

00:15:04.603 --> 00:15:06.338 align:start size:75% position:25%
<i> it looks normal,
 so, uh,</i>

00:15:06.438 --> 00:15:10.843 align:start size:91% position:9%
<i> it's not easy to say,
 well, there is the problem.</i>

00:15:10.943 --> 00:15:12.945 align:start size:84% position:16%
We can see that
there are abnormalities

00:15:13.045 --> 00:15:14.579
in the basal ganglia.

00:15:14.679 --> 00:15:18.250 align:start size:88% position:13%
These are the deep,
deep nuclei in the brain,

00:15:18.350 --> 00:15:21.787
and, uh, we have evidence,
for example, that there is

00:15:21.887 --> 00:15:25.356 align:start size:78% position:22%
an abnormality
of dopamine release

00:15:25.456 --> 00:15:27.759 align:start size:81% position:19%
<i> in the basal ganglia
 with movement.</i>

00:15:27.859 --> 00:15:29.394
There are abnormalities also

00:15:29.495 --> 00:15:31.496 align:start size:88% position:13%
in other
neurotransmitter systems

00:15:31.596 --> 00:15:33.332
such as, uh, GABA,

00:15:33.432 --> 00:15:35.967 align:start size:84% position:16%
which is an inhibitory
neurotransmitter.

00:15:36.067 --> 00:15:39.805
So we are beginning
to identify problems.

00:15:39.905 --> 00:15:42.808
<i> The best treatment options
 that we have at the moment,</i>

00:15:42.908 --> 00:15:45.377
<i> uh, relate to
 focal injections</i>

00:15:45.477 --> 00:15:47.345
<i> of botulinum neurotoxin,</i>

00:15:47.445 --> 00:15:49.214 align:start size:88% position:13%
<i> and so it's
 a symptomatic treatment.</i>

00:15:49.314 --> 00:15:52.884
It is not an ideological
treatment for the disorder,

00:15:52.984 --> 00:15:55.787
but it can help.

00:15:55.888 --> 00:15:57.156 align:start size:81% position:19%
<i> There are some people
 that are probably</i>

00:15:57.256 --> 00:16:00.125
<i> predisposed to this.</i>

00:16:00.225 --> 00:16:02.594 align:start size:81% position:19%
<i> Dystonia like almost
 anything else</i>

00:16:02.694 --> 00:16:04.496
<i> is not a single cause.</i>

00:16:04.596 --> 00:16:06.465
<i> There are probably
 multiple causes.</i>

00:16:06.565 --> 00:16:16.642 align:start size:6% position:94% line:0%
♪♪

